Tanzanian singer Ommy Dimpoz has joined the Sony Music Entertainment Africa Family. Speaking about the deal, Sony Music Entertainment Africa MD Sean Watson said they are proud to have Ommy partner with them. "We’re excited about joining forces with him to bring his amazing music to the ears of as many fans as we can. Ommy said he is excited to join Sony Music Africa. "This partnership is a very important step in my music career at the right time in my life, to see my growth and diversity in the music career. I am looking forward to a great partnership and a very successful venture with Sony Music Africa." Ommy dropped his new single and music video titled Dede featuring natives DJ Tira, Dladla Mshunqisi and Prince Bulo.